commit.message: Upgrade setup for bdist_wheel and declare it universal
More clear what's placeholders with lowercase Ys

Clean up Travis config

Really most to push something so that Travis runs.
bump version to 1.3.0, updated CHANGES, added __version__ to module.
make sure week arithmetics preserve the Week class
Include link to the Wikipedia article
Let days() return a list.  It's probably cheaper than an iterator anyways.

Don't provide iterator for the object directly

Since the object itself is a namedtuple it's not possible to override
the __getitem__ without causing problem and without it it doesn't feel
right to have the object behave as a list of days.  And writing it out as:

   for day in week.days():
       ...

   if week.contains(day):
       ...

doesn't look bad at all.
Containment test to match the iterator
Make it possible to iterate over the days in a week
Use explicit floor division where we mean it
Test for ValueError in various contexts
Add min/max/resolution attibutes to Week (like datetime.date has)

Constructor failed for week 53 in years with 53 weeks

Week(2009, 53) recursed forever :-(
